      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Base treatment of the following <i>α</i>,<i>β</i>-unsaturated carbonyl compound yields an anion by removal of H<sup>+</sup> from the <i>γ</i> carbon. Why are hydrogens on the <i>γ</i> carbon atom acidic?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaXdZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--123a94a2f5912fa14843266bfc407f1548421430/OChem_22_EC_032.jpg\" alt=\"An alpha-beta unsaturated carbonyl compound reacts with L D A to yield a carbonyl compound comprising an anion with a set of lone pairs on gamma carbon.\">",
